20. quem contra. morem maiorum minorem annis sexaginta de ponte in Tiberim deiecerit: the centuries composing the comitia centuriata voted in the Campus Martius; and the voters passed by means of pontes or narrow railed galleries to their separate voting compartments (consaepta), of which there was one for each century. The centuries in each class consisted of iuniores (from 18 to 45 years of age) and of seniores (from 46 to 60).
